   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>A War Fought by Antichrist with His Followers</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Directly against Christ with His Overcomers</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The war of Armageddon will be fought by Antichrist with his followers directly against Christ with His overcomers Rev 19:19, 11, 14; 17:14 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Antichrist, the embodiment of Satan, will be the commander of Satan's army, and Christ, the embodiment of God, will be the Commander of God's army.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Thus, on the one hand, it will be a devilish war; on the other hand, it will be a divine war.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In this divine war, Christ will destroy Antichrist "by the breath of His mouth" and bring him to nothing "by the manifestation of His coming" 2 Thes 2:8 .</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>These are the weapons Christ will use to defeat Antichrist.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>6.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>A War That Will Be the Great Winepress</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>of the Fury of God Trodden by Christ</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>This war will be the great winepress of the fury of God trodden by Christ at His coming back to judge the world Rev 14:17-20; Isa 63:1-6 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>So many evil ones who hate God will join Antichrist in fighting against God.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>When these evil ones are gathered to Armageddon, they will actually be the grapes to be trodden by God in the winepress of the fury of His wrath.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>In bringing his armies and so many evil ones together, Antichrist will actually be doing a work for God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>7.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The Nations That Participate</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Being Gathered Also by Jehovah God</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The nations that will participate in that international war against Jerusalem will be gathered also by God.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Half of the city of Jerusalem will be brought into captivity, but the rest of the people will not be cut off from the city Zech 14:2 .</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In His mercy God will still preserve half of His elect people.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>8.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Jehovah Making Jerusalem</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>a Cup of Reeling and a Burdensome Stone</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>to All the Besieging Peoples</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Jehovah will make Jerusalem a cup of reeling and a burdensome stone to all the besieging peoples, that is, to the armies of Antichrist and to all the evil ones with him.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>God will cause their horses to be bewildered and blind and their riders to be mad 12:2-4 .</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Jerusalem will need divine protection not only against Antichrist and his armies but also against Satan and his demons and evil spirits.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>We may not know how God will make Jerusalem a cup of reeling and a burdensome stone, but we know that He will do this.</S>
   </TEXT>
